                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record has been found of the discussion at this meeting, which is
                    described in Eden, <ref target="#pg_466">p. 466</ref>. Eden states that he and
                    Hopkins discussed the proposed tripartite meeting with the Soviet Union and the
                    subjects in which that country was most interested—the second front, the western
                    frontiers of the Soviet Union, and the postwar treatment of Germany.</p>
            </div>
